instruction:
Given $u(x, y) = x^3 + 6x^2y - 3xy^2 - 2y^3$, find the analytic function $f(z) = u + \mathrm{i} v$ that satisfies the condition $f(0) = 0$.

Options:
A. $$
( 6+4 \mathrm{i} ) z^{5}
$$
B. $$
( 4-5 \mathrm{i} ) z^{6}
$$
C. $$
( 1-2 \mathrm{i} ) z^{3}
$$
D. $$
( 2+ \mathrm{i} ) z^{3}
$$
E. $$
( 5+3 \mathrm{i} ) z^{7}
$$
F. $$
( 1+2 \mathrm{i} ) z^{2}
$$
G. $$
( 2- \mathrm{i} ) z^{8}
$$
H. $$
( 3-2 \mathrm{i} ) z^{2}
$$
I. $$
( 2-3 \mathrm{i} ) z^{4}
$$
J. $$
( 3+4 \mathrm{i} ) z^{5}
$$
